<section class="hero">
  <div class="wrap">
    <span class="eyebrow">CoverCapy &middot; Carrier guide</span>
    <h1>Delta Dental Patient Direct, explained</h1>
    <p class="lead">A dental discount card from the largest dental brand in the country. It is not insurance, and importantly, it is not the same as DeltaCare USA. Availability and savings vary by region.</p>
    <div class="facts">
      <div class="fact"><div class="l">Type</div><div class="v">Discount card</div><div class="s">Not insurance</div></div>
      <div class="fact"><div class="l">Savings</div><div class="v">15 to 45%+</div><div class="s">Varies by region</div></div>
      <div class="fact"><div class="l">Cost</div><div class="v">Under $9/mo</div><div class="s">~$99/yr in some regions</div></div>
      <div class="fact"><div class="l">Availability</div><div class="v">Regional</div><div class="s">Varies by Delta member company</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="verdict">
      <h4>The honest verdict</h4>
      <p>Patient Direct is a low cost, brand trusted discount card, best for healthy or infrequent dental users and for anyone facing an immediate big procedure who would otherwise hit a PPO waiting period or annual cap. If you use preventive care regularly, a PPO that covers cleanings at or near 100 percent usually wins, since with Patient Direct you still pay the discounted fee yourself. First, check that it is offered in your region.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-cta">
      <a href="#estimator" class="btn btn-primary">Estimate your savings</a>
      <a href="#verify" class="btn btn-ghost">Check if my dentist accepts it</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="band">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head"><span class="eyebrow">Read this first</span><h2>Patient Direct is not DeltaCare USA</h2><p class="lead" style="margin-top:14px">The single most important clarification. Both carry the Delta name and both say no maximums or waiting periods, which is exactly why people confuse them.</p></div>
    <div class="vs">
      <div class="col win"><h3>Patient Direct</h3><ul class="flist"><li>A dental discount program, not insurance.</li><li>You pay a small annual fee, then pay the dentist a discounted fee yourself.</li><li>Choose any participating Patient Direct dentist, no primary dentist required.</li><li>Delta pays the dentist nothing.</li></ul></div>
      <div class="col ppo"><h3>DeltaCare USA</h3><ul class="flist"><li>Dental insurance, a prepaid DHMO.</li><li>You pay a premium plus fixed copayments.</li><li>You select a primary care dentist and get referrals for specialists.</li><li>It is insurance, with covered benefits.</li></ul></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head"><span class="eyebrow">What it is</span><h2>A brand trusted discount card</h2></div>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div class="card"><span class="k">1</span><h3>You pay the discounted fee</h3><p>You pay the participating dentist a reduced, pre negotiated fee at the time of service. No claims, no reimbursement, no annual maximum, no waiting periods, no deductible.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><span class="k">2</span><h3>Backed by Delta Dental</h3><p>Patient Direct uses Delta negotiated rates and the recognition of the largest dental benefits brand in the country. Brand trust is its core selling point versus generic cards.</p></div>
      <div class="card flag"><span class="k">3</span><h3>Regional availability</h3><p>Each Delta Dental member company runs its own program, network, discount levels, and rules on whether individuals or only employer groups can buy. Confirmed in some states, not offered in others.</p></div>
      <div class="card flag"><span class="k">4</span><h3>State limited discounts</h3><p>The discount is only valid at participating dentists in the issuing state. A separate, smaller network than Delta's large PPO and Premier networks, so select Patient Direct when searching for a dentist.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

