<section>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head"><span class="eyebrow">vs a PPO</span><h2>When it beats a PPO, and when it does not</h2></div>
    <div class="vs">
      <div class="col win"><h3>Patient Direct wins when</h3><ul class="flist"><li>You want a very low fixed annual cost and few monthly premiums.</li><li>Your teeth are relatively healthy and care is occasional.</li><li>You need an immediate big procedure that would hit a PPO waiting period or annual cap.</li><li>You want the Delta brand and Delta negotiated rates.</li></ul></div>
      <div class="col ppo"><h3>A PPO wins when</h3><ul class="flist"><li>You use preventive care regularly, which insurance often covers near 100 percent.</li><li>You expect moderate, predictable spend that stays under the annual maximum.</li><li>You value true risk transfer rather than just a lower sticker price.</li></ul></div>
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top:18px; color:var(--ink-soft)">Compare real PPO plans, including Delta Dental, on <a href="/compare-ppo-dental-plans">compare PPO dental plans</a>.</p>
